humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the report, 'Multiple (4) left axillary sentinel lymph nodes without blue dye are negative for metastatic carcinoma [AJCC pNO (i-)]. Immunohistochemical cytokeratin stain was performed on the paraffin embedded sentinel lymph node tissue and confirms the H&E impression.' This indicates that no metastatic carcinoma was found in the sentinel lymph nodes. Therefore, based on New Rule 10 and New Rule 11, the N stage is N0.
